          <Comment>For these reasons, this variant has been classified as Pathogenic. This sequence change results in a premature translational stop signal in the SMAD4 gene (p.Pro470Leufs*6). While this is not anticipated to result in nonsense mediated decay, it is expected to disrupt the last 83 amino acids of the SMAD4 protein. This variant is not present in population databases (ExAC no frequency). This variant has not been reported in the literature in individuals with SMAD4-related disease. A different truncation (p.His530Thrfs*47) that lies downstream of this variant has been determined to be pathogenic (PMID: 18178612, Invitae). This suggests that deletion of this region of the SMAD4 protein is causative of disease.</Comment>
